5. A sociis. By ‘ socii ' here are meant the Peloponuesian league against Athens. Towards the close of the Peloponnesian war, 407 B.C., Lysander was sent from Sparta to take the command on the coast of Asia, to oppose Alcibiades, who was at the head of the Athenian forces. He was an officer of great diplomatic talents, and was especially commissioned to gain the favour of Cyrus, brother of Artaxerxes, king of Persia, who was then in supreme command on the coast of Asia Minor.
